This paper discusses a procedure for making collective choices through approval-preferential voting, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a new procedure, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for implementing the revised approval choice. The paper's focus on making sure a good choice is made rather than aiming for the best choice aligns with the interests of the machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
